Node.Notes: Probably members of the heavenly court, angels.
Either splendor or ornamental clothing, so "in the splendor of holiness" or "in holy attire."
Tree assumes "he makes them skip [i.e., shakes them so much that it looks like they are skipping] like a calf, [he makes the mountains of] Lebanon and Mount Hermon [skip] like sons of wild oxen."
Since conjoined with Sirion, perhaps refers to mountains of Lebanon more specifically, rather than the country itself.
Some revocalize to oaks, but hinds preferable.
Uncertain. Perhaps everyone in the temple (whether heavenly court or temple in Jerusalem is not certain).
